## Why This Happens

Supabase Edge Functions bundle everything together when deploying. If you reference a file in `index.tsx`:

```typescript
import { financialRoutes } from "./financial-connections.tsx";
```

The file `financial-connections.tsx` MUST be in the same folder during deployment.

---

## Which Solution Should I Use?

### Use Solution 1 (Inline) if:
- ✅ You want it working quickly
- ✅ You don't mind a larger `index.tsx` file
- ✅ You're not planning major changes

### Use Solution 2 (Separate Files) if:
- ✅ You want cleaner, more maintainable code
- ✅ You're okay with managing multiple files
- ✅ You plan to expand financial features

---

## Quick Test After Deployment

```bash
# Test the endpoint
curl https://your-project.supabase.co/functions/v1/make-server-8c22500c/financial/debug-config

# Should return:
{
  "stripeConfigured": true,  # or false
  "plaidConfigured": false   # or true
}
```

If you see this response, it worked! 🎉

